	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_4304381">Simple solution.<br> <br>Use the Mac like it's supposed to be used, not like a damned windows box.<br> <br>When you close a terminal window, use Apple+W, NOT Apple+Q.  Mac's are document-based, not application-based.  Close the window, not the terminal app.<br> <br>Now, when you click on the terminal again it will open up a new window in a fraction of the time.<br> <br>Justin Dubs</div>
